                    "description": "This is a board game that facilitates group learning on the rules, negotiations, and competition that surrounds natural resources planning.   \nThis new scenario is developed by a team from the International Water Management Institute (IWMI), in collaboration with Karen Environmental and Social Action Network (KESAN), Rulal: Wetlands has a wetland at its heart. It is based on recent field study of collective action and conflict resolution in Daw Lar Lake, Karen State, Myanmar, yet the issues at stake, the different roles, and the learning experience would apply to any tropical wetland, traditionally managed as a common resource. Aimed at professionals and stakeholders that are involved in natural resource planning,  experts, conservationists, government officials, NGOs, scientists, development workers, et cetera.   In cooperation with CGIAR's Research Program on Policies, Institutions, and Markets (PIM) and IWMI. \u00a9 2020 under a Creative Commons BY NC ND License.",
